status: Lucknow Super Giants won by 33 runs

videos.headline: Yash Thakur to Noor Ahmad, out Caught by de Kock!! Fifer for Yash Thakur and LSG win by 33 runs! 133.7kph, pace on and banged into the wicket, Noor stays leg-side to pull and top-edges it straight to de Kock at mid-on. Yash Thakur has his arms aloft and Bishnoi is the first one to hug him. Noor Ahmad c de Kock b Yash Thakur 4(2) [4s-1]

Yash Thakur to Rahul Tewatia, out Caught by Pooran!! Holes out! 124.5kph, Yash Thakur pulls his length back, Tewatia pulls it flat and straight to deep square leg. Couldn't generate much power behind it and didn't get the elevation as wel. Pooran doesn't err and that's wicket number four for Yash Thakur. Rahul Tewatia c Pooran b Yash Thakur 30(25) [4s-2 6s-2]

Naveen-ul-Haq to Umesh Yadav, out Caught by de Kock!! Naveen-ul-Haq joins the party! 113.1kph, slower ball on a fullish length and Umesh Yadav shapes to slog it over midwicket. Swings hard but the bat turns at the point of impact. More height than distance. QdK comes in from long-on, settles under the skier and calmly catches it. Umesh Yadav c de Kock b Naveen-ul-Haq 2(4)

Yash Thakur to Rashid Khan, out Caught by (sub)Hooda!! Another one bites the dust! 117.3kph, slower ball on a short of a good length, Rashid Khan shimmies down the track in an attempt to slap it over the off-side. He's early into his shot and ends up toe-ending it towards mid-off where Hooda back-pedals and takes a comfortable catch. Three wickets in 11 balls for Yash Thakur! Rashid Khan c (sub)Hooda b Yash Thakur 0(3)

Yash Thakur to Shankar, out Caught by Rahul!! Edged and gone! 133.8kph, short and wide outside off, Shankar hops and flashes his bat hard to flay it over backward point. All he manages is an audible edge that's been pouched by the keeper. Shankar c Rahul b Yash Thakur 17(17) [6s-1]

Krunal Pandya to Darshan Nalkande, out Caught by Yash Thakur!! Third wicket for Pandya! 99.1kph, not a good ball by any means but he gets a wicket. Fired down leg, Nalkande flicks it straight to short fine leg where Yash Thakur crouches low to reverse-cup it. GT have now lost half their side. Darshan Nalkande c Yash Thakur b Krunal Pandya 12(11) [6s-1]

Krunal Pandya to Sharath BR, out Caught by Ayush Badoni!! Four down! 100.6kph, fullish outside off and Sharath BR gets down low to play a premeditated sweep shot. This one might have held onto the pitch a bit. Lobs up in the air off the top-edge and Badoni comes in from deep backward square leg to gobble it up. Second wicket in the over for Krunal Pandya. Sharath BR c Ayush Badoni b Krunal Pandya 2(5)

Krunal Pandya to Sai Sudharsan, out Caught by Ravi Bishnoi!! Holes out! 100.3kph, short of length, Sai Sudharsan rocks back to pull and loses his shape in the process. Bit of extra bounce and he top-edges it to deep midwicket where Bishnoi takes a safe catch. GT have lost their top three within a span of 14 deliveries. Game on! Sai Sudharsan c Ravi Bishnoi b Krunal Pandya 31(23) [4s-4]

Krunal Pandya to Sai Sudharsan, out Caught by Ravi Bishnoi!! Holes out! 100.3kph, short of length, Sai Sudharsan rocks back to pull and loses his shape in the process. Bit of extra bounce and he top-edges it to deep midwicket where Bishnoi takes a safe catch. GT have lost their top three within a span of 14 deliveries. Game on! Sai Sudharsan c Ravi Bishnoi b Krunal Pandya 31(23) [4s-4]

Ravi Bishnoi to Williamson, out Caught&Bowled!! Ravi Bishnoi takes a one-handed screamer! 97.7kph, another in-drifter, fullish in length and Williamson gets forward to on-drive. Doesn't quite get to the pitch of the delivery and ends up chipping it in the air. Bishnoi flies to his right in his followthrough and sticks his right hand out to snaffle it out of thin air. Throws the ball in the air, gets up and has his arms aloft. Williamson c and b Ravi Bishnoi 1(5)

Yash Thakur to Shubman Gill, out Bowled!! Straight through. Shubman Gill has played all around a full straight delivery, flicks and misses, was the cross-seamer and the stumps are rattled. LSG needed that wicket. It's the timeout as well. Shubman Gill b Yash Thakur 19(21) [4s-2]

Rashid Khan to Ayush Badoni, out Caught by Umesh Yadav!! Straight to deep mid-wicket. The slogsweep was on but Ayush Badoni could not get it off the middle. Rashid Khan has his first. Ayush Badoni c Umesh Yadav b Rashid Khan 20(11) [4s-3]

Darshan Nalkande to Stoinis, out Caught by Sharath BR!! Darshan Nalkande comes back well. Full on middle, Stoinis gets forward to loft and it's a thick top-edge that goes miles, Sharath BR does well to hold his composure and take it. Big wicket for Stoinis was looking to turn it on. Nalkande is pumped. Stoinis c Sharath BR b Darshan Nalkande 58(43) [4s-4 6s-2]

Darshan Nalkande to Rahul, out Caught by Rahul Tewatia!! "Power failure," quips Ian Bishop on air as soon as Rahul mistimes this. Was pitched up by the pacer and Rahul tried to go after him. Takes the aerial route and launches this towards long-on, but due to lack of timing and power behind the shot, ends up getting caught at long-on. Tewatia the fielder who takes the skier as the LSG captain walks back after playing a scratchy knock. Did a decent job of rebuilding the innings though. Rahul c Rahul Tewatia b Darshan Nalkande 33(31) [4s-3]

Umesh Yadav to Padikkal, out Caught by Shankar!! Edged and taken! Umesh inflicting early damage with the new ball. Was a back of a length delivery outside off, shaping away from the batter and Padikkal played away from his body. Chases it with lack of footwork and the outside edge flies to the lone slip fielder. Shankar stationed there takes a good low catch and Padikkal's string of low scores continues.. Padikkal c Shankar b Umesh Yadav 7(7) [4s-1]

Umesh Yadav to de Kock, out Caught by Noor Ahmad!! Umesh Yadav has the last laugh! A length delivery around off, slides along the deck and de Kock gets a top edge as he looks to whip this across the line. Noor at third man settles under the skier and completes a safe catch as GT have struck in the first over. No de Kock special tonight as he walks back after hitting the only six. de Kock c Noor Ahmad b Umesh Yadav 6(4) [6s-1]
